KwaZulu-Natal police are searching for suspects who allegedly shot and killed a man at Chatsworth south of Durban. Police spokesperson Thulani Zwane says it is believed that the man was on his way to buy bread, when he was attacked by unknown gunmen. “The police were called to attend to the shooting and on their arrival they found a man lying next to the road with gunshot wounds to his head and body. Therefore they’ve opened a case of murder for further investigation. The motive of his killing is still unknown at this stage. We’re also appealing to anyone who might have information as to the where about of these suspects, who allegedly shot and killed a man to come forward and give us information,” says Zwane.